      "id": "/page/2/TextInlineMath/7",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">c<i>.</i> The informed trader can implicitly observe <i>Z</i> by observing the price and backing out the influence of <i>X</i> on the price. d<i>.</i> A third approach is useful in the case of an informed trader with CARA utility: take <i>Pt</i> = <i>H (t, Ut)</i> where d<i>Ut</i> = <i>κt</i> d<i>Yt</i> for some function <i>H</i> and a nonrandom <i>κ</i> [7].</p>",
